review_title: Just keeps coming back for more. Great inexpensive caliper
reviews: I used this as my main caliper at my engineering job for 8 months. I deliberately purchased a cheap caliper because I was sure that I would destroy it in the first week. This caliper was regularly drenched in hydraulic oil, brake cleaner, axle grease, you name it. The worst time I messed it up was by getting paint on the top where the sensor is. When it starts acting up I take everything apart and clean the feelers and the body up with a chemichal stripper or brake cleaner and a scouring pad, and every time it just keeps working. For the price I’m very happy with this thing. The downside is that it is not the most accurate, and the jaws don’t line up as good as they should. There is also more play in the sliding mechanism then I would like after about 50mm. If you want a good quality caliper, then you have to spend money. For what I needed it for, however, this has been the best little caliper I have ever owned, and it might be for you too. If you don’t need the most accurate caliper in the world, then I would strongly reccomend this neoteck.

review_title: Great inexpensive upgrade for your atv
reviews: Great upgrade for my 2004 fourtrax 350es. Better airflow than OEM for sure. Should last many years to come

review_title: Works great, charges fast, smaller and lighter than many OEM chargers
reviews: Works great, charges my HP spectre flawlessly through a USB-c docking station. Is also a lot smaller and lightweight than most factory HP chargers so it’s a great portability upgrade for most laptops. Materials and quality is as expected from an OEM HP part.

review_title: Works great, quality materials, small light and portable
reviews: This works exactly as expected for me, with the added bonus of not needing to install any drivers to get things set up. Literally just plug and play. When I have the laptop charging and all the peripherals and extra screen going, the dock gets quite hot but that’s to be expected. All the materials are top quality and the cable is much more flexible than most, so it would be a good choice for someone who’s desk is crammed for space because you can contort it into any position you need. Very small and lightweight as well so it would make an excellent travel dock.

review_title: Very good carbon monoxide detector, questionable gas leak detector. Awesome quality
reviews: It’s awesome feature to have a LNG detector built in, especially for those of us with gas fireplaces, ovens, and furnaces there are so many ways for gas leaks to happen. What I don’t like is that it only alerts for gas at 25% LEL which seems very high to actually be useful, especially since this will be mounted on the floor (natural gas rises) explosive conditions could occur along the roof well before the detector picks it up at the floor. The Carbon monoxide detector however works great as expected and has very quick reaction times compared to the competition. The unit itself seems very well made from high quality materials. Makes all my other detectors seem cheap in comparison and at its pricepoint I have to give it 5 stars. The gas detection is a nice additional feature but I question its usefulness.

review_title: Too tight at first but breaks in after a while
reviews: At first it didn’t clear the CEL and seemed too tight, but after about a month it wore in perfectly and I tried clearing the CEL again and it went out for good. If it doesn’t work for you, try giving it some time. Seems to have worked for me and can’t beat the price! On a 2003 dodge Dakota 4.7

Beats wearing safety goggles where it’s permitted. Soft enough that it won’t damage plastic glasses but it is a snug fit so might just save your eyes too. I use these on a large pair of glasses so if that was a concern with these you should not worry, if anything too small frames would be bad because it wouldn’t be a snug fit
I got a big head so it’s a bit tighter than I thought it would be. Genuine carhartt quality item here though which I was worried of

review_title: Worked great in ext cab F-150
reviews: Worked great in an extended cab 2005 f-150. This should work good in most cars, as it’s a little on the short side. If your using it for several days you’ll need to keep the lower support reinflated or else it will lean to that side because of the plastic swelling. I used it to sleep 2 people on a 3 day long camping trip and it worked great. Would probably be most comfortable for 1 person. Pump that it came with worked well. I really like this thing and wish I had bought it sooner

review_title: Definitely the real thing, and my new favourite
reviews: Seems to be the real deal. This is a much less sweet and more masculine type of fragrence. I know it smells mostly of leather but personally it reminds me of the way the air smelled in the forest while me and my father were cutting black spruce. Definetly something I liked and my girlfriend seems to agree as well. Can’t really knock this other than the fact that it’s not too powerful, which isn’t a bad thing. I would rather have it be subtle and only noticed when I’m right up close to someone than get noticed across the room IMO. Also, the only time this fragrence fits is on late nights and cold days, which limits its versatility; that won’t stop me from giving this 5 stars. It deserves it. This is probably the new best fragrence I own

I buy this stuff all the time. My favourite DynaWhey is actually the strawberry kiwi because it tastes good no matter how much you use. This one is good if you like to mix it really thick with like 2 or 2 and a half scoops or more, otherwise the orange flavour tastes a bit like a vitamin C tablet. Again, if you mix it on the heavy side this balances out and I actually really enjoy it. 5/5 for all the dynawhey flavours they all mix in great without feeling sandy or chalky like some protein powders do and the flavours are all great as well
Quality enough, good signal, acoustically transparent. Everything works and I am pleased. Will update if and when something happens to it. I gotta give this 5 stars
Comes with all interior lights except for the glove box light and the vanity lights. All the lights worked and were the same colour. Not much more to ask for it looks good

Will not stop squealing. Can't get any music to play. Even when I hook it to exactly the same wires and ground as my first amp which works perfectly. Which means that this amp is at fault. Do not buy!!! With quality control like that would you risk it

For 40$ what's to complain. At first it was very quiet to the point where I almost couldn't hear it but after a week of breaking it in it has a throaty rumble to it for sure. You won't hear it from miles away but when your near it the sound is very clean and muscular. Sounds best at about 2-3000 rpm on my crown Vic. Maybe would sound better with duals. At the end of the day this is 40$ that will make your vehicle sound really decent and in my opinion that's money well spent compared to 500-1000 for a custom exhaust system. It's also worth it to note that I did experience slight but noticeably better fuel economy as well as slightly more power around 3000 rpm. Would recommend to a freind

Weird glitches here and there. Not the most user-friendly set up but all the functions are there. Can be sketchy at times. Bluetooth works great 99% of the time until one day it'll start skipping here and there and then go away for another month :/. All in all for the money this is a very respectable product. Fit perfectly in my 2007 crown Vic and have had no major problems with it in the 4 months I have owned it

Didn't work like it should have at first and I was disappointed. Tried it again tomorrow and it worked like a charm. Since then it has worked flawlessly. Definitely noticed a change in the definition of my abdominal muscles so it does yield results. Even though the quality seemed a little iffy the point is that for like 30$ it worked and better yet it got results. Earned an honest 4/5

For the price this is probably the most powerful amp you can buy. It's 45w per channel but I somehow don't believe that. I was running two subwoofers off it at full volume (I wanted to see if it had enough power to shake the house) and it burned out the wall plug the unit came with. Switched it to a laptop charger and it has been fine since. Also if you use the "tone" function once and a while the right speaker will kick out so you have to fiddle with the button a bit. Also came with a 12v cord with a fuse that you could hook up to a vehicle battery. For the price I'm definitely not complaining. Performs well to the point where it's almost scary. Would buy this again in a heartbeat. UPDATE. 1 channel has quit working, as of December 2016. Will contact seller and update again with the response

review_title: Came with everything you would need. Power wire was ...
reviews: Came with everything you would need. Power wire was a little short to put in the trunk of my sedan but I could make it work. No complaints sounds good
